@node "SScripts" "Scripts in S:"
@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Scripts in S:@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

A script is a computer language composed of a series of commands 
within a file that is capable of being executed without being 
compiled. Amiga scripts can be created and modified with a simple text 
editor.

@{"DPat" link "GUIDEDIR:Commands/DPAT.help/MAIN"}             - Adds pattern matching to double-argument commands.
@{"PCD" link "GUIDEDIR:Commands/PCD.help/MAIN"}              - Quickly switches between two directories.
@{"Shell-startup" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/shell-startup.help/MAIN"}    - CLI/Shell customization script.
@{"SPat" link "GUIDEDIR:Commands/SPAT.help/MAIN"}             - Adds pattern matching to single-argument commands.
@{"Startup-failsafe" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/STARTUP-FAILSAFE.help/MAIN"} - Failsafe initialization script.
@{"Startup-sequence" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/STARTUP-SEQUENCE.help/MAIN"} - System initialization script.
@{"User-startup" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/USER-STARTUP.help/MAIN"}     - User customizable script.
@{"Win" link "GUIDEDIR:Commands/WIN.help/MAIN"}              - Opens Workbench windows from CLI/Shell.

@endnode
@node "AHelpSu" "Help and Support"
@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}What to do when the unexpected happens@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

  If you find a bug or have troubles using AmigaOS 3.2, please make sure 
  you first read the @{"Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)" link "GUIDEDIR:FAQ.readme/MAIN"} section as it may
  already hold the answer you might be looking for. 

  However, if you still find you cannot solve your issues, you are more 
  than encouraged to join the official AmigaOS 3.2 support forum which 
  is available at:

  http://hyperion-entertainment.com

   
@{b}Hint: Also if you press the Amiga HELP keyboard key, this very same 
      guide will automatically open.@{ub}
@endnode
@node "Aerroid" "Amiga Error Codes"
@{b}@{u}@{fg shine}Amiga Error Code Identification@{fg text}@{ub}@{uu}

The Amiga has several methods to signal the occurrence of anomalies in 
various different ways depending on the status of the Operating System 
and its hardware.

The following sections are an attempt to guide the user into 
recognizing and finding their probable cause.  

@{"Amiga Boot Color Error Codes" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/COLORERROR.help/MAIN"}
@{"Alerts or 'Guru Meditation' Errors" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/ALERTERROR.help/MAIN"}
@{"AmigaDOS Error Codes" link "GUIDEDIR:Other/DOSERROR.help/MAIN"}

@endnode
